   323→## [0.4.0] - 2017-12-24
   324→
   325→The changes in this release include cleanup of some obscure functionality and a more robust public
   326→API designed to support bridges to other logging systems, and provide more flexibility to new
   327→features in the future.
   329→### Compatibility
   330→
   331→Vast portions of the Rust ecosystem use the 0.3.x release series of log, and we don't want to force
   332→the community to go through the pain of upgrading every crate to 0.4.x at the exact same time. Along
   333→with 0.4.0, we've published a new 0.3.9 release which acts as a "shim" over 0.4.0. This will allow
   334→crates using either version to coexist without losing messages from one side or the other.
   345→### New
   346→
   347→* The crate is now `no_std` by default.
   348→* `Level` and `LevelFilter` now implement `Serialize` and `Deserialize` when the `serde` feature is
   349→    enabled.
   350→* The `Record` and `Metadata` types can now be constructed by third-party code via a builder API.
   351→* The `logger` free function returns a reference to the logger implementation. This, along with the
   352→    ability to construct `Record`s, makes it possible to bridge from another logging framework to
   353→    this one without digging into the private internals of the crate. The standard `error!` `warn!`,
   354→    etc., macros now exclusively use the public API of the crate rather than "secret" internal APIs.
   355→* `Log::flush` has been added to allow crates to tell the logging implementation to ensure that all
   356→    "in flight" log events have been persisted. This can be used, for example, just before an
   357→    application exits to ensure that asynchronous log sinks finish their work.
   359→### Removed
   360→
   361→* The `shutdown` and `shutdown_raw` functions have been removed. Supporting shutdown significantly
   362→    complicated the implementation and imposed a performance cost on each logging operation.
   363→* The `log_panics` function and its associated `nightly` Cargo feature have been removed. Use the
   364→    [log-panics](https://crates.io/crates/log-panics) instead.
   366→### Changed
   367→
   368→* The `Log` prefix has been removed from type names. For example, `LogLevelFilter` is now
   369→    `LevelFilter`, and `LogRecord` is now `Record`.
   370→* The `MaxLogLevelFilter` object has been removed in favor of a `set_max_level` free function.
   371→* The `set_logger` free functions have been restructured. The logger is now directly passed to the
   372→    functions rather than a closure which returns the logger. `set_logger` now takes a `&'static
   373→    Log` and is usable in `no_std` contexts in place of the old `set_logger_raw`. `set_boxed_logger`
   374→    is a convenience function which takes a `Box<Log>` but otherwise acts like `set_logger`. It
   375→    requires the `std` feature.
   376→* The `file` and `module_path` values in `Record` no longer have the `'static` lifetime to support
   377→    integration with other logging frameworks that don't provide a `'static` lifetime for the
   378→    equivalent values.
   379→* The `file`, `line`, and `module_path` values in `Record` are now `Option`s to support integration
   380→    with other logging frameworks that don't provide those values.
   382→### In the Future
   383→
   384→* We're looking to add support for *structured* logging - the inclusion of extra key-value pairs of
   385→    information in a log event in addition to the normal string message. This should be able to be
   386→    added in a backwards compatible manner to the 0.4.x series when the design is worked out.
   388→## Older
   389→
   390→Look at the [release tags] for information about older releases.
